items.script: What do we do? What do we do? Try to live. Go. John, go! Carrie, I'm not leaving you. I'm not leaving John. Carrie!
items.summary: A person in distress is trying to stay with others who are also distressed or unable to leave (Carrie and/or John), while someone else is urging them to escape (implied by 'Go') as they try to make sense of their current situation

items.script: Oh, God. Oh, no. Oh, God. Oh.
items.summary: A person in distress or experiencing panic is expressing their emotions with cries for help to what appears to be a dire or unfortunate situation.
